msgid "mastery.ranks.private.title"
msgstr "Private"

msgid "mastery.ranks.private.description"
msgstr "The layout has only just entered service: the base is there, but the hands still check themselves on almost every hard transition."

msgid "mastery.ranks.private.rewardTitle"
msgstr "Formation entry"

msgid "mastery.ranks.private.rewardDescription"
msgstr "The layout gets its own profile status and starts building an explicit mastery chain from the very first stable attempts."

msgid "mastery.ranks.corporal.title"
msgstr "Corporal"

msgid "mastery.ranks.corporal.description"
msgstr "The first movements are becoming reliable: the layout is recognized without extra pauses, and heavy misses happen much less often."

msgid "mastery.ranks.corporal.rewardTitle"
msgstr "First sign of stability"

msgid "mastery.ranks.corporal.rewardDescription"
msgstr "The profile begins to see that this layout has moved beyond random tries and is actually taking root in regular practice."

msgid "mastery.ranks.sergeant.title"
msgstr "Sergeant"

msgid "mastery.ranks.sergeant.description"
msgstr "The base is anchored: the user starts controlling weak spots better, and pace no longer collapses on every difficult combination."

msgid "mastery.ranks.sergeant.rewardTitle"
msgstr "Weak-spot control"

msgid "mastery.ranks.sergeant.rewardDescription"
msgstr "Mastery starts highlighting more precisely which letters, bigrams, and rhythm drops still separate the layout from the next rank."

msgid "mastery.ranks.lieutenant.title"
msgstr "Lieutenant"

msgid "mastery.ranks.lieutenant.description"
msgstr "Pace can already be called manageable: the layout holds in regular practice and does not fall apart at the first rise in difficulty."

msgid "mastery.ranks.lieutenant.rewardTitle"
msgstr "Controllable pace"

msgid "mastery.ranks.lieutenant.rewardDescription"
msgstr "Results on this layout become stable enough to show not just the fact of progress, but its quality from session to session."

msgid "mastery.ranks.captain.title"
msgstr "Captain"

msgid "mastery.ranks.captain.description"
msgstr "The user confidently carries long stretches, returns to working rhythm faster after mistakes, and reads weak zones more clearly."

msgid "mastery.ranks.captain.rewardTitle"
msgstr "Post-attempt analysis"

msgid "mastery.ranks.captain.rewardDescription"
msgstr "Progress becomes much easier to read after attempts: expanded progress analysis turns into part of steady growth rather than a rare spike."

msgid "mastery.ranks.major.title"
msgstr "Major"

msgid "mastery.ranks.major.description"
msgstr "The skill works steadily over distance: results depend less on luck and repeat more often across different modes and materials."

msgid "mastery.ranks.major.rewardTitle"
msgstr "Distance stability"

msgid "mastery.ranks.major.rewardDescription"
msgstr "The layout gains the status of a reliable field unit: long runs and regular practice start feeding the same meta-progression."

msgid "mastery.ranks.colonel.title"
msgstr "Colonel"

msgid "mastery.ranks.colonel.description"
msgstr "The layout becomes one of the core ones: high pace is paired with discipline, and input quality stays intact even under pressure."

msgid "mastery.ranks.colonel.rewardTitle"
msgstr "Core layout"

msgid "mastery.ranks.colonel.rewardDescription"
msgstr "The profile starts treating this layout as one of the leading ones and highlights it as a mature, nearly fully fielded skill."

msgid "mastery.ranks.colonel-general.title"
msgstr "Colonel General"

msgid "mastery.ranks.colonel-general.description"
msgstr "Maximum rank: the layout is fully mastered and holds pace, accuracy, and stability as a standard instrument ready for any further meta progression."

msgid "mastery.ranks.colonel-general.rewardTitle"
msgstr "Full field deployment"

msgid "mastery.ranks.colonel-general.rewardDescription"
msgstr "The layout is considered fully brought into service and can be marked as one of the most mastered in the profile’s future development."

